explanations.reason: The paper focuses on examining the robustness of the week-day effect in stock market indices using econometric methods, specifically analyzing the impact of error distributional assumptions on mean and conditional volatility. It does not mention or involve any machine learning techniques, algorithms, or models, nor does it discuss any related concepts such as supervised learning, unsupervised learning, neural networks, or any other keywords from the provided list. The study is purely econometric in nature, dealing with financial time series analysis and volatility modeling.
